MCQ format: For questions already in MCQ format, keep original choices. For non-MCQ questions, generate 3 plausible distractors programmatically: (a) for factual questions, use other entities from the same category (e.g., other capitals, other elements), (b) for math questions, use common wrong answers (off-by-one, wrong operation), (c) randomize correct answer position (A/B/C/D) using seed-based shuffling. Template: 'Question: {q}
A) {opt1}
B) {opt2}
C) {opt3}
D) {opt4}
Answer:'
